Ad Text:
Join our Downer Professional Services team and play a key role in delivering complex defence and national security projects that safeguard Australia's future.

Downer Professional Services comprises of three business units our Technical, Advisory, and Capability consulting practice, and Team Downer, which partners with CASG and NSSG as a major service provider to Defence. Together, we are a multi-disciplinary advisory and delivery partner of choice for clients across Defence and National Security.

We currently have an opportunity for a Senior Strategic Implementation Business Analyst in Melbourne to work on CASG Commercial Division Projects.

What You'll Do

This role offers a broad scope, with key role responsibilities including:



Shape and deliver the Commercial Team's strategic roadmap by developing forward work plans and operational artefacts that translate strategy into actionable tasks.




Coordinate the development of a structured information framework that supports policy, process, and knowledge management for the new S/4HANA ERP environment.




Collaborate across Defence stakeholders to ensure seamless end‑to‑end integration of procurement processes with broader ERP workstreams.




Conduct analytical and investigative work to identify business requirements, process improvements, and opportunities for system enhancement within the Defence ERP program.




Drive adoption of the new ERP system by identifying uplift needs in policy, process, training, and change management, while supporting effective procurement outcomes through strong stakeholder engagement.






What You'll Bring




Hands‑on experience navigating and performing transactional activities in SAP S/4HANA, ideally within commercial or procurement modules.




Demonstrated capability working with senior executives and operating effectively in complex public‑sector environments.




Background in procurement or commercial functions, preferably within Defence or other government settings.




Strong stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to build relationships across diverse teams and industry partners.




Proven ability to work independently, exercise sound judgment, and communicate clearly in both written and verbal forms.


Due to the nature of the work, you are required to currently hold and maintain a minimum Baseline, with ability to obtain Negative Vetting 1 or higher Security clearance as required by the Commonwealth. In some instances, compliance with International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR) requirements may also be an inherent requirement.

More than anything, you'll bring a strong work ethic, a positive attitude, and a commitment to delivering high-quality outcomes for our clients.



Why Downer Professional Services



At Downer Professional Services, we're not just a workplace - we're a business dedicated to contributing to the shaping of the future of defence in Australia. As the country's only sovereign prime, we're committed to making a real difference in protecting Australia's interests.

What is means to belong at Downer Professional Services

Meaningful work: Help to deliver critical Defence projects that protect Australia and shape its future.


Professional development: Access career mapping, accelerated learning programs, and shared learning through our Communities of Practice.


Great perks: Enjoy discounts on healthcare, retail, vehicles, and more through Perks@Downer.


Veteran support: Benefit from initiatives like up to 20 days of Reservist Leave to stay connected post-service.

You want your work to matter and so do we. With over 26,000 people across Australia, New Zealand and the Pacific, our team is made up of individuals with unique perspectives, backgrounds, and ideas.
We know that diversity makes us stronger and we actively celebrate it through our commitment to inclusion and belonging.

We're committed to building a team that reflects the diverse communities we serve and we welcome people of all ages, genders, sexual orientations, cultures, abilities, and lived experiences. We especially encourage applications from those whose voices have traditionally been underrepresented in our industry, including women, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples, Māori and Pasifika Peoples, veterans, people with disability, and neurodivergent individuals. Even if your experience doesn't align perfectly with this role, we'd still like to hear from you. If it feels like the right fit, apply - potential counts, and so do you.

As a WORK180 Endorsed Employer, we support flexibility that works for your life, inclusive leadership that values your voice, and equitable access to opportunity so you can do your best work and bring your whole self to it.


If you need support or adjustments through the recruitment process, just let us know, we're here to help you put your best foot forward.

Ad Text:
Key competencies (role specific criteria):

Understanding of the range of data produced from the technical, scientific, instrumental and clinical aspects of pathology laboratories.  
Understanding of ETL (Extract, Transform and Load) in a large production data warehouse environment. Demonstrated experience in creating data models involving SCD (slowly changing data).
Strong experience in Data management, Programming and Documentation as well as quality control activities including prototyping, beta testing, and user acceptance testing.
Experience working with BI technology and LIS applications such as SaS, AUSLAB, DSS Necto, Qlik and other business intelligence tools. Must have a strong command of Power BI Desktop, Power Query, DAX, SQL and query folding.
Demonstrated experience with business process modelling and improvement techniques as well as identify requirements, write specifications, manage, and trace requirements, conduct investment analysis and work with vendors, enterprise architects and subject matter experts within a Digital and ICT context.
Experience with stakeholder engagement and communication skills, including the ability to prepare proposals, work packages and business cases to influence the decision making of senior staff. 
Good communication and interpersonal skills with a diplomatic approach and the ability to liaise and relate to a wide range of stakeholders including senior and executive stakeholders.
Motivated and proactive with the ability to manage and coordinate work within a multi-disciplinary team with limited supervision.

Why work with us? 

Work alongside passionate professionals in a supportive and inclusive environment that values people and prioritises employee success and wellbeing. This includes

Competitive salaries

•    12.75% superannuation 
•    17.5% leave loading

Employee wellbeing

•    Access to 24/7 confidential employee support providers and counsellors including for immediate family members
•    Additional flexibility to support your work life balance including access to generous leave entitlements, such as purchased leave, domestic violence leave, reproductive health leave, cultural leave, study and examination leave.

Professional development

•    Career progression with more than 300 diverse career pathways and career support to take you further! 
•    Access to a variety of programs and initiatives to support training and career growth. 
•    Grow your skills through hands-on experience and access to internal training opportunities and additional financial and leave benefits for approved external training and development.

Our commitment to equity, diversity and inclusion 

At Queensland Health, our work environment is inclusive and supportive, and we value our employees. We are an equal opportunity employer and encourage applications from people of all cultures, abilities and backgrounds. 

Our commitment to cultural safety, equity, diversity and inclusion means we understand some people may need changes to the recruitment process. If you need support during the recruitment process, such as meeting with the panel virtually instead of in person, please reach out to the hiring manager. We value diverse candidates and your need for adjustments will not affect our hiring decisions.

Job Title: Senior Manager Planning and Digital Partnering
Ad Text:
Melbourne (Bundoora)  Full-Time HEO10 Fixed-term September 2027

Are you a strategic thinker with a passion for shaping digital transformation across a complex organisation?  Do you excel at partnering with senior leaders to influence long-term digital direction and enterprise planning?

La Trobe University is seeking an experienced and dynamic leader to join the Information Services Division as Senior Manager, Planning and Digital Partnering. In this pivotal role, you will act as a trusted advisor to university leaders—ensuring digital initiatives are aligned with strategic priorities, fostering strong relationships across academic and professional areas, and guiding enterprise-wide planning and roadmap development.

This position is ideally suited to professionals with backgrounds such as Senior Business Analyst, Project Manager, IT operational specialist, or similar roles who are ready to step into a strategic partnering position focused on future-state planning, demand management, and strategic alignment.

Please note: This is not a project or program delivery role—it focuses on pre-project strategy, planning, and enterprise engagement.

In this pivotal role, you will:

Lead integrated planning to align digital initiatives with La Trobe’s strategic priorities
Act as a trusted advisor to senior leadership and university stakeholders
Shape and support the development of La Trobe’s digital strategy
Drive demand management, digital solution identification, and continuous improvement
Lead and develop a high-performing team and influence university-wide engagement

We’re looking for someone with:

Proven strategic planning and digital transformation experience
Strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills
A deep understanding of digital technologies, platforms, and trends
Experience managing complex projects and resources in a large organisation
The ability to collaborate, influence and drive cultural and operational change

La Trobe offers a flexible, inclusive, and purpose-driven environment where your contributions will help shape the digital future of higher education.

Benefits:

17% employer contributed superannuation
On site child care facilities
Flexible work arrangements
Discounts for staff and their family members to study a range of La Trobe courses

Financial Model & Reporting Analyst

Iberdrola Australia - VNI West Project | Melbourne

Permanent | Full-time | High-impact infrastructure investment role | Global exposure


About the Company

Davidson is proud to be partnering with Iberdrola, a global renewable energy powerhouse operating in more than 40 countries and driving the transition to clean, reliable, affordable energy. In Australia, Iberdrola has invested over $5 billion across wind, solar, batteries, hydrogen and major transmission projects.

VNI West is a landmark transmission project that will connect Victoria and NSW, strengthening the grid and enabling Australia's renewable energy future. As a key delivery partner, Iberdrola is expanding its Investment Office and seeking a Financial Model & Reporting Analyst to support the development and oversight of the project's investment model.

About the role

Reporting directly to the Project Investment Lead, you will play a pivotal role in developing and maintaining the core investment model that underpins VNI West's commercial structure, government engagement and internal decision-making.

This role is suited to someone who is technically strong, analytically sharp and curious, with a passion for infrastructure economics, energy markets or large-scale capital projects. You will work alongside a dynamic investment and strategy team, collaborating with senior stakeholders in Australia and Iberdrola's global offices.

Build, adapt and maintain complex financial models that meet both government and Iberdrola requirements.
Incorporate construction, operational, tax, debt, valuation and risk inputs, including scenario and sensitivity analysis.
Ensure models are robust, auditable and ready for review by government and external consultants.
Prepare investment papers, financial summaries, commercial assessments and Board-ready reporting.
Translate model outputs into clear, commercially relevant insights for senior leaders.
Collaborate with Finance, Risk, Commercial, Control and the Investment Office, as well as global teams in Spain.
Work with government partners, financial/technical advisors and other external stakeholders.
Contribute to commercial structures, pricing mechanisms and value-driver analysis.
Provide inputs for pre-construction and PMO teams as required.
Support key project milestones including submissions, audits and investment reviews.

About you

Essential

Experience in energy, infrastructure, utilities, Big 4 transactions or investment teams
At least 2-4 years' experience in financial modelling, project finance, infrastructure investment, valuation, M&A or treasury
Strong Excel capability, including scenarios, sensitivities and macros/VBA
Solid understanding of financial, accounting and valuation metrics
Fast learner with strong problem-solving ability and attention to detail
Clear communicator who works well with others


Highly Regarded

Exposure to government tenders, regulated assets or major capital projects
Qualifications such as CFA or Master of Applied Finance
Experience in international or global organisations
Strong PowerPoint skills and ability to prepare commercial presentations


Personal Attributes

Easy-going, proactive and collaborative
Strong commercial intuition and comfortable asking questions
Adaptable in fast-paced, shifting environments
Team-focused, helpful and solution-oriented

The Benefits

Work on one of the most significant energy infrastructure projects in Australia.
Direct exposure to senior leaders, government partners and global project teams.
Be part of a mission-driven organisation accelerating the clean energy transition.
Access to global expertise, European capability and world-class development standards.
Career pathways across investment, strategy, M&A, energy markets and international rotations.

Location & Flexibility

Based in Melbourne CBD on-site
Occasional travel to Sydney and internal workshops.
Flexibility required for meetings across time zones, particularly with Spain.

How to Apply

If you're an emerging investment or financial modelling professional looking for an opportunity where your work genuinely shapes the future of Australia's energy system, we'd love to hear from you.

Apply now or reach out for a confidential discussion.

Please apply with current resume in Microsoft Word format only (.doc or .docx). If you would like to have a confidential discussion, please contact William Stock on william.stock@davidsonwp.com quoting reference JN -112025-41902. Want to know more about Davidson? Visit us at www.davidsonwp.com

The Company

This is a fantastic opportunity to join a leading insurance organisation recognised among the top five general insurers in Australia and New Zealand.

With a focus on innovation, inclusion, and customer outcomes, this company is reshaping the future of insurance through data-led decisions and people-first leadership. Enjoy modern hybrid working options and a forward-thinking culture that values your growth.

The Role

As a Finance Business Partner, you will play a key role in supporting the strategic and commercial goals of the business. Leading a team of 1–2 analysts, you’ll be responsible for delivering financial insights, performance analysis, and high-impact business support.

Your responsibilities will include:

Acting as a trusted advisor to business units, delivering financial analysis and insights to drive strategic decisions
Presenting financial results to senior leadership, offering recommendations and commentary
Leading the end-to-end budgeting and forecasting process (P&L, Balance Sheet, Cash Flow)
Supporting board and committee reporting, as well as key external stakeholder reports (e.g. shareholders, rating agencies)
Managing legal entity reporting including transfer pricing and reconciliation
Enhancing FP&A systems and processes, with a focus on reporting automation and self-service through tools like PowerBI
Delivering ad hoc financial modelling and valuation support for strategic initiatives
The Candidate

Experience: CA/CPA (or equivalent) with strong business partnering, FP&A, or commercial finance experience. Insurance industry knowledge and familiarity with AASB 17 are essential.
Leadership: Demonstrated experience leading teams and influencing senior stakeholders.
Technical Skills: Strong financial modelling, analysis, and reporting capabilities with advanced Excel and PowerBI experience.
Personal Attributes: Commercially savvy, driven, confident in stakeholder engagement, and able to thrive in a fast-paced, deadline-driven environment.
To learn more, please apply now or send your updated CV to josh@lansonpartners.com.

Superannuation fund with a large team in Sydney are looking for a new person to join their Investment Team. This fund have significant accolades for their investment performance and take risk very seriously.

Job Title: Senior Analyst, Development New Business and Structured Products
Ad Text:
More than 50 years ago a foundation was laid, with a vision for the future. To re-imagine the environments where Australians would live, work and grow. In this time, Mirvac has evolved from a small joint venture to a thriving ASX-listed property group, leading in sustainability, innovation, safety, and placemaking.

Mirvac has created some of Australia's most iconic places, from thriving residential communities, to landmark offices and mixed-use precincts. At the heart of every project: a deep commitment to our customers, and an ambition to reimagine urban life.

At Mirvac, we know that it's our people, their passion and expertise and the exceptional experiences we create for our audience, that defines us.

Our opportunity

We have an opportunity for a Senior Analyst, New Business & Structured Transactions to join our team. You will primarily support the Commercial & Mixed-use New Business function (predominantly mixed use development commercial and living orientated developments) as well as supporting the Product Origination and Structured Projects or Build to Rent New Business Analyst team as required, to facilitate the growth of development pipeline.

The Commercial & Mixed-use New Business function is an integral part of Mirvac, tasked with replenishing Mirvac's large development pipeline and converting new projects in preparation for delivery. The Product Origination and Structured Projects team secures new capital sources to assist in the delivery of Mirvac's development pipeline and investment strategies.

Your responsibilities will include:


Build and maintain financial models underpinning new business opportunities and investment strategies. This includes building development and investment models, running various scenarios as well as different transaction structures to test different strategies and producing succinct summaries of the results.
Ensure that each financial model is logic and in line with industry practice
Keep abreast of market developments, valuation assumptions and practices as well as key underwrite assumptions
Drive optimisation of the financial outcomes, assessing options and recommending strategies which underpin value and achieve a "highest and best use" analysis and best-case scenarios
Understanding of cash and capital impacts of all major decisions and investments
Ensure modelling is undertaken in a manner consistent with the proposed transaction structures
Research and analyse data to support underlying assumptions
Prepare competitor analyses and market intelligence reports

Your point of difference

You will be professionally qualified with demonstrated experience working as an Analyst within the property industry, preferably within a development or investments environment. You will have a strong capability building, amending and testing of financial models and experience working with large datasets and preparing reports and presentations.

You will be a strong communicator, with well developed analytical and problem solving skills as well as a self-motivated and inquisitive nature who thrives building and developing stakeholder relationships.

All of these attributes are preferred, if you think you may be the right fit for the role please still apply.

About the Opportunity

We’re looking for a Head of Digital Marketing to take ownership of one of Australia’s largest, most recognisable large-scale campaigns and drive its next phase of growth.
This is a senior, hands-on role for someone who lives and breathes digital marketing, performance, optimisation and engagement. The campaign is powered primarily through sophisticated EDM programs and lifecycle marketing, supported by broader ATL and BTL activity. Your mandate is clear: increase participation, deepen engagement, optimise performance and grow revenue.

You’ll sit at the intersection of strategy and execution. While you’ll set the direction and lead a capable team, this is not a purely advisory role. You’ll stay close to the tools, the data and the detail, particularly during peak campaign periods.
If you thrive in fast-paced, campaign-driven environments and are energised by scale, complexity and measurable outcomes, this is a genuinely rare opportunity.

What You’ll Lead In this senior, specialist role, you will:

Own the end-to-end digital marketing and growth strategy for a large-scale national campaign, spanning both Above the Line and Below the Line activity.
Lead the supporter and participant journey, with a strong focus on EDMs, lifecycle marketing, segmentation, testing and conversion optimisation.
Drive engagement and revenue growth through data-led decision making, continuous optimisation and performance marketing best practice.
Remain hands-on across key platforms including Campaign Monitor, Mailchimp, Iterable, Google Analytics and PowerBI.
Translate complex performance data into clear insights that inform strategy, prioritisation and investment decisions.
Lead and develop a high-performing team, including a Marketing 2IC overseeing email, lifecycle and conversion specialists.
Systemise and scale marketing operations to ensure the team performs under pressure during peak campaign cycles.
Partner closely with senior leadership and cross-functional teams to align marketing activity with commercial and growth objectives.
Bring new ideas, technologies and approaches to the table to continually lift performance and keep the campaign ahead of the curve.
About You You’re a digitally fluent marketing leader who combines strategic thinking with deep technical capability. You’re as comfortable in PowerBI and GA as you are shaping a campaign narrative or coaching a team.

You’ll be well suited to this role if you:

Have 8+ years’ experience in digital marketing, growth or performance-led marketing roles.
Are highly experienced in EDM-driven campaigns, lifecycle marketing and conversion optimisation at scale.
Have hands-on experience with Campaign Monitor, Mailchimp, Iterable, Google Analytics and PowerBI.
Understand how to balance ATL brand activity with BTL performance channels.
Are commercially minded and motivated by measurable outcomes, engagement metrics and revenue growth.
Can confidently lead, mentor and develop specialists while staying close to execution yourself.
Thrive in fast-paced, deadline-driven environments, particularly during major campaign periods.
Care deeply about building strong systems, processes and team capability.
What’s On Offer
A senior leadership role with real ownership and influence over a nationally recognised campaign.
The opportunity to drive large-scale engagement and revenue through sophisticated digital marketing.
Close collaboration with executive leadership and direct input into growth strategy.
A high-calibre team and the chance to mentor a strong Marketing 2IC.
A dynamic, ambitious culture that values innovation, performance and accountability.

Shape and execute Origin's digital sales roadmap, ensuring alignment with business goals
Drive digital growth and innovation, shaping the future of Origin's sales stategy
Melbourne CBD based

Join a team that's All Kinds of Useful

At Origin, being useful is more than a tagline - it's how we approach work every day. As a collective, we're a team that thrives on finding better ways, working together, and owning our impact. From powering homes to delivering award-winning internet and helping to lead Australia's energy transition. If you're driven by purpose and excited to be part of something bigger, we'd love to have you on the journey.

About the role:


As the Senior Digital Insights Analyst, you'll play a pivotal role in helping Origin deliver a leading digital sales experience that customers love.

Sitting within the Digital Sales team, you'll leverage your deep expertise in Adobe Digital Analytics and a strong data-driven mindset to uncover opportunities that increase digital performance, conversion and adoption.

You'll partner closely with Product, Design and Delivery teams to provide clear, actionable insights that inform prioritisation, shape solutions to key customer and business challenges, and measure the impact of digital improvements.

Your ability to translate complex data into compelling narratives and practical recommendations will be critical in optimising our digital ecosystem and driving meaningful commercial outcomes.

Roles & Responsibilities

Analyze data from Adobe Analytics and other sources to identify trends, uncover opportunities and optimize digital sales performance.
Provide clear actionable insights that improve website and app conversion, engagement and customer experience.
Support the prioritisation of high-impact initiatives by connecting data- insights with business objectives and customer outcomes.
Clearly frame problems and opportunities, translating insights for effective digital solution definition.
Lead analytics implementation, including Adobe Launch tracking, and enhance Tableau dashboard capabilities.
Develop performance reporting, track key digital KPIs, and ensure the benefits of digital initiatives are clearly measured and realized.
Collaborate with key stakeholders (product, marketing, sales & operations) to align insights to digital targets and go to market activity.
Champion a culture of continuous improvement, data-led decision making and performance visibility across the Digital team & wider business.

What will you bring?

You will have a Bachelor's degree in Analytics, Statistics, Computer Science or a related field paired with 5 years + experience in digital analytics, specializing in Adobe Digital Analytics.

Analyse complex data sets to extract actionable insights.
Strong understanding of web analytics, conversion funnels, and attribution modelling.
Proficient in SQL or eager to develop SQL skills; experienced with Power BI or Tableau.
Excellent communication and presentation skills for non-technical stakeholders.
Understand cost, ROI, and link digital experiences to business outcomes.
Committed to enhancing customer experiences through digital solutions.
Thrive in fast-paced, agile environments, collaborating with diverse teams and managing competing priorities.

So, why join us?

Thrive in a culture of personal and professional growth.
Enjoy a central CBD location with access to parking and public transport.
Engage in opportunities through the Origin Foundation to support your community.
Powering your career with unbeatable perks - Get discounted electricity, gas, and internet as an Origin employee.
Explore unique and cost-effective employee EV Car subscriptions.

At Origin, we're powered by people who believe in creating change.

Enjoy a challenging career in an exciting industry where you can grow and explore your potential. If you think you have transferable skills, an appetite to learn and would be a great fit, we'd love to hear from you.

About the role
We’re seeking a Communications Specialist to lead the delivery of stakeholder engagement and communication initiatives within a large-scale ERP Program. Acting as the key conduit between the Change Lead and Change Analysts, you’ll ensure consistency, quality, and alignment so that engagement, artefacts and messaging are fit‑for‑purpose and business‑ready.

What you’ll do


Develop and implement stakeholder engagement and communication plans to support ERP initiatives and drive understanding across impacted groups.
Lead, coordinate, and complete first review of all engagement and communication materials to ensure consistency in tone, style, and messaging across all channels.
Liaise directly with the Business Process Team Business Analyst to coordinate business engagement meetings; facilitate sessions with the Business Process Team as required.
Maintain and manage stakeholder engagement tracking tools (e.g., registers, calendars, dashboards).
Act as the primary contact for Change Analysts, providing guidance on engagement processes, templates, and delivery standards.
Monitor and report on stakeholder engagement activities, providing insights on readiness, adoption progress, and communication effectiveness.
Support change readiness activities, including stakeholder analysis and feedback loops to continuously refine engagement strategies.
Participate in business engagement sessions; present updates on stakeholder engagement and communications where required.
About you

If you live in Australia or New Zealand, you've likely heard of AMP. But at a time when society is changing, we are too. We're now a nimbler business with new leadership and thinking.

For us, these are exciting times. There's a real potential for big thinkers to help us redefine what financial services could be. And turn our legacy into something even more positive and powerful for the future.

Help people create their tomorrow, while you create yours

We help people with their banking, super, retirement and finances. Through upturns, downturns, recessions, and major life transitions. Every day, we help people see and make more of their financial potential, so that they can create their tomorrow. And we've been doing it for over 170 years.

If we do our job well, we genuinely add to the prosperity of our country and its people.

How you'll make an impact

The Lead Business Analyst brings deep subject matter expertise in Wealth Management and Superannuation and is responsible for consulting with business and technology leaders to create their strategy and associated delivery roadmaps.

As Lead Business Analyst, reporting into the Delivery Manager, you will be responsible for creating and defining innovative solutions and leading the work of for team of Business Analysts.

You'll have a comprehensive understanding of the Business Analysis practices, own and drive the analysis process for the North Platform and form a business analysis community centred around continuous improvement.

As a leader in creating solutions to meet business problems, you'll be a key person for value streams their business executives and leadership teams.

What you'll bring to the role


Business partnerships and strategy development. Consult with technology and business leaders to create solutions to drive the delivery of their strategy.
Responsible for leading and directing analysis activities for an initiative, including leading the work of Business Analysts within a delivery squad.
Custodian of the Business Analysis practice, processes and tools, forming a community of practice to oversee and improve the way Business Analysis is performed.
Govern and oversee a delivery squad's analysis, documentation and processes follow set out standards, are of the highest quality (balancing efficiency) and maintain consistency over time and across the team.
Drive continuous improvement in the delivery team's analysis output and provides constructive feedback and coaching to the team that fosters ongoing improvement.
Lead delivery risk assessment and is responsible for identifying, raising, reporting and mitigating risks involved in and discovered through analysis activities.
Lead the adoption of business agility, and delivery within an Agile framework, facilitating ceremonies (e.g. standups, retros) ensuring progress and continuous improvement.
Part of the values stream leadership team working with Delivery Managers, Project Managers and Tech Leads in analysis planning, tracking and reporting activity from project and squad through to portfolio level.
Leads the business in forming scope and initial estimates for new development ideas and proposals, contributing deep knowledge and coordinating technical experts where needed.
Actively engages in analysis while also coordinating analysis work across the Business Analysis team to navigate complex challenges and enable efficient and effective delivery. Supports hiring and responsible for onboarding Business Analysts through mentoring and 'buddying'.

You'll thrive here if…

If you can adapt from BAU to the ambiguous with ease, you'll do well here. Change is never easy, so bring your commitment, grit and growth mindset.

Because we run lean, you'll be expected to jump in and deliver across a variety of areas. Meaning, you'll be closer to the action and executive decisions that influence where we go next.

If you're someone that can hold their own, you'll find AMP quite liberating.

Why we think you'll love working at AMP

Doing what we've always done is not an option, so your clever ideas will get airtime here. You'll be encouraged to speak up and try new things. If they don't work, we move on - better for it.

We know there's no one way of doing things. So, you won't have to sacrifice who you are or how you work to fit in here. We're inclusive and flexible in many of the ways you'd expect. And in some of the ways you wouldn't. As long as your health and wellbeing come first - at home and at work.

In fact, most of what makes AMP such a welcoming, enjoyable place to work are our people. Wherever you go, you'll find moments to connect, feel valued and do meaningful work.

Whether it's through our first-class leaders who are invested in you and your success. Through year-round opportunities to volunteer, fundraise and give back to the community. Or in the everyday challenges you face as we work together to strengthen this great organisation. Challenges that will stretch you, amplify your potential and compound the impact you have.

We believe in the power of inclusion and diversity

We're dedicated to fostering inclusion, diversity, and a warm feeling of belonging at AMP. It sparks creativity, ignites innovation, and turns up the dial on the quality of our decisions and performance. This not only makes our workplace more engaged, but also leads to better connections with our customers.

We're your allies in the search for the perfect fit - when you apply, let us know how we can support you to put your best self forward during our selection process.

We're also committed to enhancing employment opportunities for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, so we enthusiastically encourage candidates from these backgrounds to apply and explore our Reconciliation Plan on our website

Ready to create your tomorrow?

If you're someone who sees opportunity where others see challenge, come and work with us in smart, progressive ways as we transform an iconic Australian brand for the future. And, through a series of career-defining moments, create your own tomorrow.

Don't procrastinate! We review applications when we get them, and if we discover the ideal candidate, we may close the role earlier than the advertised close date.
